                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Wikipedia presents Euler’s identity as the equation\ne^{iπ} + 1 = 0,\nwhich is a special case (x = π) of Euler’s formula e^{ix} = cos x + i sin x. Using cos π = −1 and sin π = 0 gives e^{iπ} = −1, hence e^{iπ} + 1 = 0. The article highlights that the identity links five fundamental constants (0, 1, π, e, i), is named after Leonhard Euler, and is often cited as an exemplar of mathematical beauty.",
